# Encryption and keys

## Field-level encryption (prisma-field-encryption)

- Annotated fields in app/prisma/schema.prisma with /// @encrypted (and optional /// @encryption:hash(...)) are transparently encrypted
- Generated migration helpers under app/prisma/reencrypt/* (and microservice/prisma/reencrypt/*) support re-encrypting data across key rotations
- DB key material is provided via env (DB_ENCRYPTION_KEY plus optional DB_DECRYPTION_KEY_* for old keys). In K8S, these live in the SECRET_DB secret (see .deploy/dineros.template.yaml)

## Key rotation strategies

- In staging, a CronJob (key-rotation-cronjob.template.yaml) runs nightly using the microservice :keyrotate image to:
  - Patch DB secret with a new encryption key (append-only, preserving prior decryption keys)
  - Restart Deployments to pick up keys
  - Call microservice /migrate to run reencrypt migrators (microservice/routes/migrate.post.ts)
- Microservice routes for rotation/migration: migrate.get.ts and migrate.post.ts (operational endpoints)

## Post-restore local workflows

- See docs/post-restore-encryption-plan.md and scripts/reset-encrypted-users-after-restore.ts
  - After restoring prod/staging data locally without source key, placeholders overwrite sensitive fields (plaid tokens nulled, friendly names for registers/entries/reoccurrences, dev emails)
  - If source encryption key is provided (e.g., DINEROS_STAGING_DB_ENCRYPTION_KEY), use generated reencrypt migration to decrypt+re-encrypt into local key, then optionally reset local users to dev accounts

## RSA and JWT

- RSA keypairs stored in Rsa model (rotateable, with isDefault flag)
- RsaService and JwtService in app/server/services/* manage cryptographic operations (see tests under services/__tests__/RsaService.test.ts and JwtService.test.ts)

## Rate limiting and auth factors

- Redis-backed rate limiting helper: app/server/lib/rateLimitRedis.ts
- MFA: TOTP (otplib) and WebAuthn passkeys under app/server/api/mfa/* and server/lib/mfa.ts

## Safety notes

- Never commit real keys or secrets; .pre-commit-config.yaml enforces checks (TruffleHog, block .env)
- For CI tests, minimal fake keys are provided via env in workflows (e.g., PLAID_CLIENT_ID=ci-test)
